-- REPLACE INTO `STANDARD_MONSTERS` VALUES (160,'Guardian Naga','Large','monstrosity','','lawful good','18','127','15d10','40 ft.','19','18','16','16','19','18','','8','7','7','8','8.0','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','Celestial, Common','darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 14','10','','','poison','charmed, poisoned','<html><br><li><br><name><text><b>Rejuvenation</text></name><br><desc><text><i>If it dies, the naga returns to life in 1d6 days and regains all its hit points. Only a wish spell can prevent this trait from functioning.</text></desc><br><attack_bonus>0</attack_bonus><br></li><br><li><br><name><text><b>Spellcasting</text></name><br><desc><text><i>The naga is an 11th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is Wisdom (spell save DC 16, +8 to hit with spell attacks), and it needs only verbal components to cast its spells. It has the following cleric spells prepared:

